## 4. Container Responsibilities

### Nginx
- Listens on port 443
- Handles SSL/TLS
- Routes requests to containers
- Does NOT expose backend services directly

### WordPress
- Runs PHP-FPM
- Processes dynamic content
- Connects to MariaDB and Redis

### MariaDB
- Stores WordPress data
- Uses persistent volume

### Redis
- Provides caching layer
- Improves performance

### Adminer
- Web UI for database management

### cAdvisor
- Collects container metrics:
  - CPU
  - Memory
  - Network

### FTP
- Allows external file access to WordPress volume

