## 12. Common Pitfalls

### 1. Wrong Routing
WordPress catches all requests if `location /` is not configured properly

### 2. Missing Trailing Slash
`/cadvisor` vs `/cadvisor/` can break routing

### 3. Port Confusion
- Internal: container ports (e.g. 8080)
- External: only 443 exposed

### 4. DNS Issues
Container names must match service names

